HEADWORD: Breastband
<hw>Breast"band`</hw> <pr>(-b⟦acr⟧nd`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A band
for the breast. Specifically: <fld>(Naut.)</fld> A band of canvas, or a
rope, fastened at both ends to the rigging, to support the man who
heaves the lead in sounding.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

